					<main id="main" class="site-main" role="main">
																	
	<article id="post-7089" class="post-7089 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-business category-culture category-hotels category-hotels-specials category-news category-specials category-tourism tag-bali-hotel-with-futon tag-bali-news tag-hoshinoya-hotel tag-japanese-style-hotel-in-bali tag-rie-azuma tag-takaaki-yasuda tag-tirta-empul tag-ubud-hotel">
		<header class="entry-header">
			<h1 class="entry-title">Yokoso! Hoshinoya Hotel Opens in Bali</h1>
			<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="cat-links"><i class="fa fa-folder"></i> <a href="https://balidiscovery.com/category/news/business/" rel="category tag">Business</a>, <a href="https://balidiscovery.com/category/news/culture/" rel="category tag">Culture</a>, <a href="https://balidiscovery.com/category/news/business/hotels/" rel="category tag">Hotels</a>, <a href="https://balidiscovery.com/category/specials/hotels-specials/" rel="category tag">Hotels</a>, <a href="https://balidiscovery.com/category/news/" rel="category tag">News</a>, <a href="https://balidiscovery.com/category/specials/" rel="category tag">Special Offers</a>, <a href="https://balidiscovery.com/category/news/business/tourism/" rel="category tag">Tourism</a></span><span class="posted-on"><i class="fa fa-clock-o"></i> <a href="https://balidiscovery.com/yokoso-hoshinoya-hotel-opens-in-bali/" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date published">June 27, 2021</span><span class="updated sr-only">June 27, 2021</span></a></span><span class="byline"> <i class="fa fa-user"></i> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn" href="https://balidiscovery.com/author/jack-daniels/">J. M. Daniels</a></span></span>			</div>
		</header>

				<div class="entry-thumbnail"><img width="1024" height="649" src="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1-1.jpg" class="attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="" srcset="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1-1.jpg 1024w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1-1-205x130.jpg 205w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1-1-568x360.jpg 568w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1-1-768x487.jpg 768w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1-1-230x146.jpg 230w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"/></div>
	
	<div class="row">
		<div class="entry-content col-md-9 col-md-push-3">
			
<p>A Japanese-style hotel with 30 villas opens in Bali in July 2021.</p>



<p><em>The Hoshinoya Hotel&#8217;s&nbsp;</em>opening demonstrates resilient faith in Bali and the future of the Island&#8217;s tourism industry by its opening during the continuing global pandemic.</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img loading="lazy" src="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshilogo.png" alt="" class="wp-image-7090" width="311" height="223" srcset="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshilogo.png 265w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshilogo-181x130.png 181w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshilogo-230x165.png 230w" sizes="(max-width: 311px) 100vw, 311px"/></figure></div>



<p><strong>Seeking to Be at One with Nature</strong></p>



<p>Takaaki Yasuda, general manager of the new Hotel, said on Thursday, 24 June 2021: &#8220;The Hoshinoya Bali Resort is surrounded by nature and the Pakerisan River, which forms a part of Balinese mythology. We are here as a retreat from the busy working day to provide a peaceful and meditative locale to restore and refresh the spirituality of our guests.&#8221;</p>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="512" height="288" src="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiareal.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-7098" srcset="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiareal.jpg 512w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiareal-230x129.jpg 230w" sizes="(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px"/></figure></div>



<p>Bali&#8217;s sacred water source &#8211; the Tirta Empul River on the slopes of Mount Batur, feeds the Pakerisan River that provides the constant soothing sound of flowing water that permeates the Resort. The&nbsp;<em>Hoshinoya&nbsp;</em>is also surrounded by a&nbsp;<em>subak-fed</em>&nbsp;irrigation system, in place for more than 1,000 years and underlining the Balinese reverence for water and sharing God&#8217;s natural gifts bestowed on humanity.</p>



<p><em>The Hoshinoya Resort&nbsp;</em>seeks to become a place of peace and rest removed from the maddening crowd and the hectic pace of the modern world. Guests are free to visit temples, walkthrough verdant rice fields, sit beneath shady trees, cycle, meditate, eat healthy food and explore the interesting village of Ubud, Bali.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped"><ul class="blocks-gallery-grid"><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img loading="lazy" width="568" height="360" src="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1-568x360.jpg" alt="" data-id="7091" data-full-url="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1.jpg" data-link="https://balidiscovery.com/?attachment_id=7091" class="wp-image-7091" srcset="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1-568x360.jpg 568w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1-205x130.jpg 205w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1-768x487.jpg 768w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1-230x146.jpg 230w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi1.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 568px) 100vw, 568px"/></figure></li><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img loading="lazy" width="259" height="194" src="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi2.jpg" alt="" data-id="7092" data-full-url="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi2.jpg" data-link="https://balidiscovery.com/?attachment_id=7092" class="wp-image-7092" srcset="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi2.jpg 259w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi2-174x130.jpg 174w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi2-230x172.jpg 230w" sizes="(max-width: 259px) 100vw, 259px"/></figure></li><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img loading="lazy" width="540" height="360" src="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi3-540x360.jpg" alt="" data-id="7093" data-full-url="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi3.jpg" data-link="https://balidiscovery.com/?attachment_id=7093" class="wp-image-7093" srcset="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi3-540x360.jpg 540w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi3-195x130.jpg 195w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi3-230x153.jpg 230w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi3.jpg 1500w" sizes="(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px"/></figure></li><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img loading="lazy" width="539" height="360" src="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi4-539x360.jpg" alt="" data-id="7094" data-full-url="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi4.jpg" data-link="https://balidiscovery.com/?attachment_id=7094" class="wp-image-7094" srcset="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi4-539x360.jpg 539w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi4-195x130.jpg 195w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi4-768x513.jpg 768w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi4-230x154.jpg 230w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshi4.jpg 1498w" sizes="(max-width: 539px) 100vw, 539px"/></figure></li></ul></figure>



<p>The Hotel&#8217;s interior features traditional Japanese sleeping arrangements on a&nbsp;<em>futon.&nbsp;</em>Balinese finishes such as wooden carvings and batik adorn surfaces in the rooms. The entire Resort is designed by renowned Japanese architect Rie Azuma with the 30 villas having individually distinct designs reflecting their named villa category of&nbsp;<em>Bulan, Soka,&nbsp;</em>and&nbsp;<em>Jalak.</em></p>



<p>The entire Resort lightly occupies a 3-hectare site that includes jungled areas, terraced rice fields, and temples.</p>



<p><strong>Hotel Embraces Tri Hita Karana Philosophy</strong></p>



<p>Mindful of the Balinese philosophy of&nbsp;<em>Tri Hita Karana&nbsp;</em>–&nbsp;<em>The Hoshinoya&nbsp;</em>strives to maintain a balance between man and nature, man and his neighbor, and between man and his Maker.</p>



<p><em>The Hoshinoya</em>&nbsp;is the first Hotel built by the Japanese company outside Japan.&nbsp;<em>Hoshino Resorts</em>&nbsp;operated hotels and&nbsp;<em>ryokan (Japanese Inns)&nbsp;</em>from its Japanese base. Established in 1904, it opened its first hot-water Resort in Karuizawa in 1914. Today it operates five separate accommodation brands:&nbsp;<em>Hoshinoya, Kai, Risonare, Omo</em>, and&nbsp;<em>Beb.&nbsp;</em></p>



<figure class="wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped"><ul class="blocks-gallery-grid"><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img loading="lazy" width="290" height="174" src="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint.jpg" alt="" data-id="7095" data-full-url="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint.jpg" data-link="https://balidiscovery.com/?attachment_id=7095" class="wp-image-7095" srcset="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint.jpg 290w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint-217x130.jpg 217w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint-230x138.jpg 230w" sizes="(max-width: 290px) 100vw, 290px"/></figure></li><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img loading="lazy" width="540" height="360" src="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint1-540x360.jpg" alt="" data-id="7096" data-full-url="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint1.jpg" data-link="https://balidiscovery.com/?attachment_id=7096" class="wp-image-7096" srcset="https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint1-540x360.jpg 540w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint1-195x130.jpg 195w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint1-230x153.jpg 230w, https://balidiscovery.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/hoshiint1.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px"/></figure></li></ul></figure>



<p>In all<em>, Hoshina</em>&nbsp;manages 45 properties in Japan.</p>



<p>Each villa comprising the Resort faces a semi-private pool. The roof of each villa is made of natural materials combining Ulin wood and&nbsp;<em>alang-alang thatching</em>. Each villa has its own private garden space, created for reading or quiet contemplation.</p>



<p>The décor, furniture, accent carvings, and even eating utensils reflect the talent of local artists and craftsmen.</p>



<p>In combinations, the results are at once stunning, inspiring, and comforting.</p>



<p><strong>Hishinoya Resort Bali</strong></p>



<p>Banjar. Pengembungan, Desa Pejeng Kangin</p>



<p>Kecamatan Tampaksiring, Gianyar 80552 Bali, Indonesia</p>



<p><a href="https://hoshinoya.com/bali/en/">Hoshinoya Resort Website</a></p>
						</div>
